snippet: Prime Minister David Cameron promised tax cuts, new “starter homes” for first-time buyers under 40 and no spending reductions for the National Health Service.
abstract: Great Britain's Prime Min David Cameron tries to rouse his Conservative Party to victory in May by promising tax cuts, new homes for first-time buyers and no spending reductions for the National Health Service.

byline.original: By STEVEN ERLANGER and STEPHEN CASTLE

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister David Cameron promised tax cuts, new “starter homes” for first-time buyers under 40 and no spending reductions for the National Health Service.

headline.main: British Leader, With Eye on Next Election, Tries to Rouse Conservative Party
